{
  "stem": "14168.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They had a horse and a buggy, and I loved that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They also-- I remember, from early childhood-- in fact, up until 1936-- whenever I went there, on Shabbat morning, I used to walk to the little town, where there was a synagogue that was 150 years old, where my father had been confirmed, had become bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And every Saturday morning, Shabbat morning, I was called to the Torah to say the blessings and sit in the same seat where my great-grandfather had been.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So that was much-- that was very enjoyable and belongs to one of my fondest memories.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes, just to give me the feeling that I was being useful.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They also-- yes, I did.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember very well, my father was with me a few times.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he had prohibited me, told me not to climb up the cherry tree, which I did.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when I was upstairs, the ladder disappeared.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I had to suffer there for about three or four hours.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I never did that again.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[LAUGHTER]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, but we had-- we had a lovely time there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I noticed one thing though, that from the very beginning on, there was tremendous anti-Semitism in Poland at that time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's-- it was very disturbing to me, and it may sound paradoxical.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Even under the German Nazi regime, at least at the early stages, there was more anti-Semitism coming from the masses than there was in Germany.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was one of the unpleasant memories that I had.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Was this in-- does this apply to Posen, or Breslau, also?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Posen was Polish.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Breslau was German.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I did, but not to the intense degree that I felt it in Poland.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
